               <msContents>
                  <summary>Ghazals followed by ruba'is, both arranged by rhyming letter. Cf. Ethe No 1601, with the same incipit after a prose preface which is absent in this MS. Apparently an early collection of the author's work.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_307-item1">
                     <author key="person_1324806" change="#ids-cleanup #role-assignment" role="aut">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Zafar Khan 'Ahsan'.</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9537">Divan of Mirza Ahsan (Better known as Zafar Khan).</title>
                     <note>F1a: a) Note of acquisition at Burhanpur in 1163 (1749-50) and loan to somebody, next to impression of rectangular seal of Mirza Nawazish Khan dated 1163. b) Verses of Nurjahan Begum, Nasir 'Ali and Jalal Asir. F1b: signature of David Price. Extra folios before and after the text contain verses, including ones attributed to Bidil, 'Ishqi and Adham. Author was governor of Kashmir and Kabul under Shahjahan.</note>
                     <incipit>Chu gardad sharmsari dar qiyamat 'udhr-khwah-i ma Ghazals followed by ruba'is, both arranged by rhyming letter. Cf. Ethe No 1601, with the same incipit after a prose preface which is absent in this MS. Apparently an early collection of the author's work.</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe No 1601.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
